        "id": "post-hrt-differences",
        "slug": "hrt-differences",
        "status": "published",
        "data": {
          "title": "Natural or synthetic HRT: understanding the difference",
          "excerpt": "Synthetic HRT and natural hormone replacement therapy for menopause symptoms are not the same - learn the differences",
          "featured_image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1505751172876-fa1923c5c528?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80",
          "content": [
            {
              "_type": "block",
              "style": "normal",
              "children": [
                {
                  "_type": "span",
                  "text": "Synthetic HRT and natural hormone replacement therapy for menopause symptoms are not the same - learn the differences in oestrogens, progesterones, and delivery methods.",
                  "_key": "s1"
                }
              ],
              "_key": "s0"
            }
          ]
        },
        "taxonomies": {
          "category": [
            "general"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "post-blood-tests-hrt",
        "slug": "blood-tests-hrt",
        "status": "published",
        "data": {
          "title": "What should I know before having a blood test while on HRT?",
          "excerpt": "Newson Clinic's guide to blood tests while on HRT, including timings, what we test, and why bone density also matters.",
          "featured_image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1579154204601-01588f351e67?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80",
          "content": [
            {
              "_type": "block",
              "style": "normal",
              "children": [
                {
                  "_type": "span",
                  "text": "Blood tests are a useful tool to monitor hormone levels, especially oestrogen and thyroid hormones, to ensure your body is receiving the optimal dosage.",
                  "_key": "b1"
                }
              ],
              "_key": "b0"
            }
          ]
        },
        "taxonomies": {
          "category": [
            "general"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "post-testosterone-benefits",
        "slug": "testosterone-benefits",
        "status": "published",
        "data": {
          "title": "What are the benefits of testosterone for women who take HRT?",
          "excerpt": "Testosterone can be taken alongside oestrogen and/or progesterone to treat perimenopausal and menopausal symptoms like brain fog, low libido, and muscle loss.",
          "featured_image": "https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1576091160399-112ba8d25d1d?auto=format&fit=crop&w=800&q=80",
          "content": [
